I used to be lazy to score restaurants on Google Maps. This is the first time I've scored a restaurant, since this sushi restaurant is the best sushi I've ever eaten in Brooklyn. The ingredients are sufficient, the rice are soft, and the fish is tender! I don't know why this store scores much lower than that of ordinary sushi stores. Is it because the store is small? But during the COVID-19, everyone would take out instead of eating in the store. The owner of the store is also very good. It’s really a great sushi restaurant! The place looks ugly, as first. I walked in and wanted to get a takeout. The waitress/hostess was wearung rubber flip flops...?? I was called to the back of the seating area where she was filling to-go sauce cups, took my order there. I was forced to take 2 rolls instead of one because I didn't have cash and their CC minimum is $10. Everything is overpriced. Regular roll is $5-$8, when in fancier places it is $3.50, the food is not out of this world at all. Wouldn't go there again for sure and advise you not to.

Miso is a traditional Japanese sushi eatery,  the restaurant is small and there's a zen vibe with soft relaxing music. The wait staff is very friendly and  courteous, they offer a range of sushi,noodles, appetizers and desserts  all of which are delicious  the prices are very affordable with decent portions. This place is great for dates or a lunch with friends  is very casual but the option is there if you want to dress up for the evening.  Overall a great place out of the way and not  so crowded. I really like the humble esthetic this place gives off definitely reccomend.

The sushi won't make you sick.  And that's the only selling point.  The food is mediocre.  You'd be lucky if the service was mediocre too.  I've been here a few times for lunch- there's always a problem. Poorly wrapped rolls-- 2 roll lunch specials that take 40 minutes to make-- sometimes the wasabi has a brown hue to it--  or like today, when my order was just plain wrong. But after already waiting most of the time i had for lunch-- i couldn't afford to wait for them to correct it. Probably wouldn't be so annoying if they didn't also charge DUMBO prices for Jersey quality sushi.  If this place wasn't the Only sushi joint in DUMBO- they'd have gone out of business a long time ago. Make your order to go-- and if you're getting delivery, order from somewhere else.
This place is fine for some fast sushi at lunch. But don't disappoint your dinner date with this D-list Dumbo diner, the food here is aggressively mediocre. 3 STARS

Miso Sushi Restaurant offers simple yet reliable sushi dishes. It's nothing to write home about but the place is nearly spotless, the service is attentive and the menu items are appropriately sized. I've had the tempura udon, premium sashimi, gyoza and veggie dumplings a few times with no complaints.

The lunch specials at Miso Sushi are a good deal- 2 rolls and a soup/salad for $8. This is the same price for a roll made by the bodegas and market delis. Wouldn't you rather get more and a side from a Japanese restaurant? Ask for your rolls to be hand rolls. They stuff them silly. More innards than what's in a regular roll.

We popped in here for a snack on New Year's Eve. We only had a sapporo and 6 pieces of Salmon Nigiri. They had already packed up their fish for closing but but they still let us in. The rice and the fish were delicious. While I cannot vouch for anything else based solely on the Salmon I will be going back to checkout what else they have to offer!
